/target

# assets/ holds three kinds of files per book:
#   - raw/        pre-curation pipeline outputs (PDF, OCR, lines,
#                 elements, raw MD) + external source binaries —
#                 regenerable, kept out of git
#   - curated/    human-edited MD (reviewed + modernized + translated)
#                 — irreplaceable editorial work, tracked
#   - derived/    auto-generated artifacts downstream of curation
#                 (struct JSONs the ingest binary loads) — regenerable
#                 from curated/ in seconds, kept out of git
#
# Bibles live flat under assets/bible/ (no curation layer; translations
# come from external public-domain sources as-is) — all ignored.
#
# The negations below re-include the curated tier per source. Add a
# `!assets/<book>/curated/` line whenever a new book gains a curated
# layer. Order matters: parent dirs must be un-ignored before children.
assets/*
!assets/LICENSE
!assets/kant1/
assets/kant1/*
!assets/kant1/curated/

.env
apps/web/node_modules/
apps/web/dist/
.turbo
node_modules
.venv
.claude/projects/
.antigravitycli

# Terraform — `.terraform/` is the local plugin/module cache that
# `terraform init` populates (vendor binaries, sometimes hundreds of
# MB). `.terraform.lock.hcl` IS tracked (it pins provider versions).
# tfstate files belong in the remote backend, never in git.
.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.backup
*.tfplan

# Exact pg_dump DDL, regenerable via `pnpm db:schema`. The companion
# schema.simplified.sql IS tracked (small, diagram-import friendly).
docs/db/schema.sql